body:
Hi there!

While a simple `0 ** 0` design like the one below works (with a = b = 0),

```
module toplevel (
  input logic a,
  input logic b,
  output logic y
);

  assign y = a ** b;

endmodule
```

a slightly more complex design:

```
module top(in_data, out_data);
  wire [3:0] signal0_;
  wire [136:0] signal1_;
  input [95:0] in_data;
  wire [95:0] in_data;
  output [95:0] out_data;
  wire [95:0] out_data;
  assign out_data[3:0] = signal0_ ** in_data[68:65];
  assign { signal1_[136:135], out_data[63:32], signal1_[102:40], signal0_, signal1_[35:0] } = { in_data[72:32], in_data } ^ { in_data[53:13], in_data };
  assign { signal1_[134:103], signal1_[39:36] } = { out_data[63:32], signal0_ };
endmodule
```
yields incorrect results.

[Here are traces for Verilator and Icarus.](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/13466641/traces.zip)

I'll look more into #4709 as it may well be related, as you mentioned in #4719.

Thanks!
